# domain-glossary local config

Copy this file to `domain-glossary.local.md` (same directory) and edit the
paths to match your machine. `*.local.md` is gitignored.

## Field reference

- `name` — domain label used by `/domain-glossary seed` and the glossary's
  storage path. Free-form string (e.g. `Altamira`, `OptinMonster`).
- `glossary` — absolute path (or `~/`-prefixed) to the glossary file in your
  Obsidian vault.
- `repos` — list of absolute repo paths that map to this domain. Longest-prefix
  match wins, so worktrees siblings (e.g. `mtf-builder-feature-x`) are caught
  automatically.

## How the skill uses this

When the agent invokes `domain-glossary` (typically because the user mentioned
an unfamiliar acronym or project-specific term), the skill:

1. Reads this config.
2. Resolves the current cwd to a domain via longest-prefix match on `repos`.
3. Reads the matching `glossary` file with the Read tool.
4. Answers grounded in entries found there, or reports "not in glossary."

No per-repo install or CLAUDE.md edits required. Add a new domain by appending
to the `domains:` list.
